SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 36-3-627(b), is amended by
redesignating the subsection as subdivision (b)(1) and adding the following new subdivision:
(2)
(A) A victim may file a petition, prior to the respondent's conviction for an
offense listed in subdivision (a)(1), with the court with criminal jurisdiction over
the respondent's trial for the offense on which the petition is based. The court
shall cause a copy of the petition to be served upon the respondent, with notice
that a hearing on the petition will be held immediately following the entry of
judgment, if the respondent is convicted of the offense on which the petition is
based; provided, however, that a hearing must not occur for at least five (5) days
from the date of service.
(B) The court must hold the petition until the conclusion of the criminal
trial. If the respondent is not convicted of the offense on which the petition is
